** The role **   
Reporting to the Manager Data Linkage, Statistical Analysis and Linkage Unit,
you will lead and design, develop, and document software applications and
their components to enhance data linkage technical infrastructure and
operations. You will also provide strategic guidance on ICT infrastructure,
software development, and technical operations within the unit's application
portfolio. The lead ensures team compliance with software development and
security standards, collaborates on project planning and scheduling, and takes
technical responsibility for iterations of the software development lifecycle.

Building effective relationships with internal and external stakeholders,
including Queensland Health teams and technology vendors, is crucial for
integrating changes, resolving production issues, and advancing the unit's
work program. Additionally, the role involves administering supporting
applications, managing cloud hosting environments, and upholding information
security policies to safeguard the confidentiality, availability, and
integrity of data.

** The successful person **   
To excel in this position, it is crucial to highlight advanced skills and
extensive experience, with a minimum of five years in an Oracle developer
role, encompassing the design, development, and administration of applications
and databases using the Oracle technology stack (SFIA: DESN Level 4, PROG
Level 5, DBDS Level 4). Demonstrated capabilities include taking technical
responsibility, resource management for planning, estimating, and executing
development work in alignment with established standards (SFIA: PEMT Level 4,
DLMG Level 5), as well as expertise in establishing processes and crafting
software to ensure the quality, security, integrity, and availability of
reporting data sets (SFIA: DATM Level 5).

Furthermore, it is essential to exhibit proven expertise in identifying and
promoting new and emerging software technologies, products, methods, and
techniques, with a keen ability to assess their relevance and potential value
(SFIA: EMRG Level 5, METL Level 5). The role also requires demonstrated
proficiency in supporting application administration, release deployment, and
providing direct technical support to users and operational groups (SFIA: ASUP
Level 5, RELM Level 5). Highly desirable is demonstrated expertise in
operations support involving Oracle database, Unix Solaris, and Cloud
provisioning (SFIA: DBAD Level 5).

Consideration of essential requirements should be coupled with a focus on key
technologies for this role, including Oracle APEX, Oracle PL/SQL (DML and
DDL), Oracle database, Data model creation, and Linux/Unix shell scripting.

** About us **   
The Department of Health is responsible for the overall management of the
public health system in Queensland. We are an organisation that strongly
believes in the need to work with people who value the goals of our
organisation and who will thrive in our workplace. Working at the Department
of Health is about making a difference.

The Healthcare Purchasing and System Performance (HPSP) Division purchases
public health and social services from service providers to optimise health
gains, reduce inequalities, and maximise the health system's efficiency and
effectiveness. HPSP ensures health funding is used effectively to meet
government priorities and achieve performance objectives outlined in
agreements and contracts arising from purchasing decisions. As part of the
commissioning role, the Division has responsibility for investing nearly $18
billion on behalf of the State and managing community services contracts to
the value of approximately $280 million.  
  
** Benefits **   
• A fast-paced, challenging and supportive environment  
• Competitive salary + generous superannuation and leave loading.  
• Flexible working arrangements  
• Diverse work culture  
• Career training and development

** How to apply **   
To apply for this opportunity:  
• Please submit your resume (including the details of two referees), and  
• A cover letter (maximum 2 pages) outlining your skills and experience
relevant for this role.

